The '''Original trilogy''' is the first installment of films of the [[Star Wars saga|''Star Wars'' saga]] to be produced. These were the movies released from [[1977]] to [[1983]]. They primarily focus on the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]] trying to free [[the galaxy]] from the clutches of the [[Galactic Empire]], as well as [[Luke Skywalker]]'s quest to become a [[Jedi]] and face [[Sith Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker|Darth Vader]] and his master, [[Galactic Emperor|Emperor]] [[Darth Sidious|Palpatine]].

The original trilogy is sometimes called the '''classic trilogy''' in contrast to the [[prequel trilogy]]. The [[sequel trilogy]] takes place 30 years after ''Return of the Jedi''.

